                            <comment id="14136964" author="hitliuyi" created="Wed, 17 Sep 2014 08:51:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You are right, HTTP 401 UNAUTHORIZED is for authentication failed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Do we need to change following to UNAUTHORIZED?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;} &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (throwable &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;instanceof&lt;/span&gt; AuthenticationException) {
      status = Response.Status.FORBIDDEN;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14137639" author="tucu00" created="Wed, 17 Sep 2014 17:56:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=hitliuyi&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;hitliuyi&quot;&gt;hitliuyi&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;tt&gt;KMSExceptionsProvider&lt;/tt&gt; only kicks when &lt;tt&gt;KMS&lt;/tt&gt; processing throws an exception. &lt;tt&gt;KMS&lt;/tt&gt; processing kicks in only if the HTTP request has been properly authenticated. The only reason you could get an &lt;tt&gt;AuthenticatioException&lt;/tt&gt; here is because the backend used by KMS throws that exception. If that happens,KMS triggering a login request won&apos;t help, thus the FORBIDDEN.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
